This paper is about document summarization, which involves natural language processing and information retrieval, suggesting that it could belong to the cs.CL (Computation and Language) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-categories. The paper also proposes two improved models that incorporate topic modeling and lifelong learning, indicating that it could also fit into the cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the use of feedback in lifelong learning, which could place it in the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category.
